metadata.name: Prophecy #287
metadata.description:
Elder Futhark Runes / Proto-Germanic alphabets flowing through the canvas.

Each iteration gets a random rune from 24 runes and the vector field angles are based on that.

Also picks one word from what the random rune symbolizes as a prophecy for the next year.

Minted for #fxhashturnsone event 18.11.2022.

50% of primary profits to Processing Foundation.

Save image with 's'.

Load 2x or 4x dimensions (2560 * 3840px) image with '2' or '4'.

metadata.name: fx_doughs #969
Azulejo #11
metadata.description:
Azulejo is a generative work made with p5.js

Behind this artwork, the author (eduxdux) had made a lot of research about tiling, the main references for this work were Athos Bulcão, Alexandre Mancini, and "Azulejo da igrejinha" by Cândido Portinari.

This artwork has 8 color palettes and 7 tile styles.
If you have lucky you can have a fully filled tile.

This work is participating in the FxHash anniversary event (#fxhashturnsone) and 10% of the royalties go to the Save Pakistan

Eduxdux November 2022

metadata.name: Geode #79
metadata.description:
A single seed shape is chosen from 13, and placed onto the plane. At every step, a copy of this seed is laid edge-to-edge adjacent to an existing shape, without causing any overlaps. This copy is colored based on the edge it shares with the existing shape. The process continues until the animation completes.

New shapes are placed closest to a moving target. In some mints, this target is slow moving, causing new shapes to expand radially from the seed. In other mints, this target races around, causing new shapes to chase it. 

Each of the 13 shapes forms different patterns under different circumstances. Not all patterns will be explored.

Controls:
  - SPACE: Pause/unpause the animation.
  - ENTER: Skip the animation.
  - R: Restart the animation.

URL Params:
  - "preview=1": Skip the animation.
  - "flex=1": Adapt the boundaries to the size of the window.
  - “slow=1”: Draw only one shape per frame.

Licensed under CC BY-NC-SA 4.0

metadata.name: CHRONUS #14
metadata.description:
Following the use of simple shapes as the main element, combined with the alternation and overlapping of layers and blending modes, "CHRONUS" adds the temporal dimension as one of the elements that form what is seen.

Furthermore, the different gradations, associated with the play of lights and shadows, reveal the unusual as an image.

Nothing is just one thing.

#Main Features
- 13 color schemes “zones”:

* Vascai, Shadow Sky and Bronze – 12,5% chance
* Burnt Golden - 10% chance
* Lemonade - 8,5% chance
* Red Browned, Rec, Tif and Soldier - 7,5% chance
* Lushtemple and 80’s – 5% chance
* BR - 2,5% chance
* B&W - 1,5% chance

- 3 canvas formats;
- 3 times of run;
- 3 patterns;
- 3 degrees of color saturation;

Obs.:
- The first 3 iterations will entitle you to 1 free edition of my next project on FxHash.
- The "STEEL" palette entitles you to 1 free edition of my next project on FxHash.
- The rendering process should take a few seconds, so enjoy the look of the circles in action.

september 14, 2022

Generative Token by Morbeck for fxhash.
